China Plans to Dam Pakistan’s Indus River for Power, FT Reports

-- B y   B i l l y   C h a n
-- 
2011-06-08T00:59:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/china-plans-to-dam-pakistan-s-indus-river-for-power-ft-reports.html
China ’s Three Gorges Project Corp.
plans to build a $15 billion hydroelectric development project
to  Pakistan , damming the  Indus River  at various points, the
Financial Times reported, citing Asim Hussain, Pakistan’s
minister for petroleum and natural resources.  Damming the river will provide electricity for Pakistan and
prevent floods, FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Billy Chan in  Hong Kong  at 
 bchan101@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
